    • Method Detail

      • __del_builtin__

        void __del_builtin__()
        __del_builtin__() is the built-in's own finalizer, while FinalizablePyObjectDerived.__del_derived__() refers to an instance's in-dict __del__. A FinalizeTrigger calls FinalizablePyObjectDerived.__del_derived__() first and - if existent - __del_builtin__() after that. A plain FinalizablePyObject.__del__() would behave as overwritten by FinalizablePyObjectDerived.__del_derived__(), i.e. won't be called if the type implements FinalizablePyObjectDerived, while __del_builtin__() is called in any case.
